  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 low-confidence honest documentation)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Evidence confidence is approximately 50% due to limited experimental replicates and wide uncertainty bounds on blood rheology inputs; these limitations are documented honestly with full rationale and a sensitivity analysis identifying the dominant uncertain inputs. The decision is Accepted with documented residual uncertainty acknowledged in the decision rationale.",
